.TH "comedi_buf_write_alloc" 9 "comedi_buf_write_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
comedi_buf_write_alloc \- Reserve buffer space for writing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" comedi_buf_write_alloc
.BI "(struct comedi_subdevice *s "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nbytes "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "s" 12
COMEDI subdevice.
.IP "nbytes" 12
Maximum space to reserve in bytes.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reserve up to \fInbytes\fP bytes of space to be written in the COMEDI acquisition
data buffer associated with the subdevice.  The amount reserved is limited
by the space available.
.SH "RETURN"
The amount of space reserved in bytes.
